Handunnettige Deepthi Priyantha Kumar Dharmasena (born 24 April 1971) 
more commonly known as Kumar Dharmasena or by his nickname Unanduwa,
is a Sri Lankan cricket umpire and former international cricketer, 
who played Tests and ODIs for Sri Lanka.
He was a key member of the Sri Lanka team that won the 1996 Cricket World Cup.
He was a right-handed batsman and a right-arm off break bowler.